rComments: Yes, his lectures are monotonous but he is a very nice and caring guy. When emailing him about a question/concern, he will respond with multiple paragraphs to make sure that you understand everything. He is available at office hours and available for appointments if you can't make it. Memorize the slides and do the readings and you will be golden.

Very shy guy and caring guy! He speaks kinda quietly making it difficult to hear sometimes. His midterms and exams are 100% fair based on the assigned readings and course content. I skimmed most of the textbook and ended up with an A on midterms so if you actually read it you should be able to get 100%

Do the readings and you'll be fine. Although a lot of people suggest not going to his classes, attending them helped reinforce the important material. He's quite monotone but you can tell he tries hard to make it engaging. I would take this class again. Easy A (if you read the text).

This is first time teaching at uottawa so you can see he's anxious. Very nice guy, soft spoken and you can see that's the kind of person he is. Information is not heavy, I rarely used the textbook. Read his slides and go to class and you will do well.
Loveeee him. Super chill probably because he's so shy. Can't bully this professor a real gem who is nervous but excited about teaching. would love to take again

Super nice prof! He's very shy and tries really hard to make the lectures as engaging and interesting as possible. Always reminds the class of his office hours. Very fair with midterms, and he goes over them and gives practice.

Exams were so fair, you don't even have to go to class, do the learning curves read the practice exam and go through his slides and you're fine! He makes the material super easy to understand and shows videos and posts them! I dunno what these other reviews are saying tbh.

honestly not bad as a prof, you can tell he tries to be engaging during the class and he really cares how well you do. After each midterm he reviews the answers which I find helpful, especially when reviewing for finals. Midterms aren't that bad, just make sure you read the textbook and review the slides
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Professor Rutt really cares about his students. He is always making sure everyone is clear on what is expected and is always available for office hours. He gives out practice questions before exams and they reflect well what is on the actual exam. Read the textbook and attend class as he emphasizes the important material to know.

Definitely need to use the textbook to do good in the class, powerpoints are hard to follow and don't have much information on them. Midterms are way harder then needed. Prof is really nice and you can tell he tries really hard to engage the class but you really dont need to go to class.
He makes the Midterms hard for no reason. No one goes to class. Memorize the textbook and you will be set. Has nothing on his slides. Late to his classes and posts power points last minute.
He wastes time , don't go to class, memorize the textbook and you'll be fine

One of the worst professors Disorganized, useless slides, he doesn't say anything useful in the class and is expecting us to answer his tricky questions promptly. He's convinced that he is teaching us in the proper way although he's not. Only one fifth or less of the class are attending his lectures because it is a waste of time. Avoid his classes

Avoid at all costs- wastes the classes time shows up late and doesn't start the lecture until 30-45mins after the lecture was supposed to start. Very disorganised lecturer and he is unable to answer students questions- saying that he doesn't know the answer to a simple psychology question that he should know.
Not the best lecturer (monotone), but his slides are decent and the online homework helps you understand the concepts. Encourages you to see him before midterm and gave good practice guide before it!

One of the worst lecturers I have had so far at this school. His thoughts are disorganized, his voice quiet, and he is unable to keep the attention of the 300 some undergrads in his classroom. Posts his slides last minute, and they also contain little to no information. Gives you no idea what to study. Avoid at all costs.
HORRIBLE

Attendance for this class was not mandatory but due to people not showing up to class Prof. Rutt sent out several announcements trying to force people to attend his class. He seems like a nice guy but he is very monotone and not specific as to what we need to know for class. His slides are always posted late and are very vague. Try a different prof

Very monotone and disorganized. Often late to class and slideshows don't make a lot of sense. Slides don't match up with readings at all, and he doesn't really give questions a straightforward answer.
Super nice guy! However, his lectures are a little disorganized and the slides are rarely posted before class, kinda just reads off the slides.
